\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 CocoaDVDPlayer
\fs46 \

\fs36 \
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The CocoaDVDPlayer project demonstrates how to play DVD-Video media in a Cocoa application using DVD Playback Services, the API for the DVD Playback framework introduced in Mac OS X 
\f2 \cb2 v
\f1 \cb1 10.3. The project builds an application with a full set of controls and a resizable video window that maintains the correct aspect ratio. Other features include bookmarks, multiple viewing angles, and a playback timer. The project also shows how to register for and handle DVD events, and how to implement error-handling.\
\
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Features
\f1\b0\fs28 \
\pard\tx360\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf0 \
Video window:\
\
	\'a5	Resizable with real-time scaling\
	\'a5	Small/Normal/Maximum sizes\
	\'a5	Two aspect ratios, standard (4:3) and wide screen (16:9)\
\
Control window:\
\
	\'a5	Audio volume slider\
	\'a5	Bookmarks\
	\'a5	Elapsed or remaining playback time\
	\'a5	Next Angle button (for titles with multiple viewing angles)\
	\'a5	Open Media Folder menu item\
	\'a5	Play/Pause/Stop/Eject buttons\
	\'a5	Previous Scene and Next Scene buttons\
	\'a5	Scan Forward and Scan Reverse (4x) buttons\
	\'a5	Title and scene information\
	\'a5	Go to Menu button\
\
\
